Peru Stocks: Candente, Cementos, Siderperu, Volcan Cia. Minera

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-08-18T20:47:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/peru-stocks-candente-cementos-siderperu-volcan-cia-minera.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index fell 2.3 percent to 19,516.14. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index dropped 2.1 percent to 2,513.30.  Industrial shares slumped on investor concern growth will
slow, said Arlen Lahura, a trader at Lima-based brokerage Coril
SAB.  Cementos Lima SA (CEMLIMI1)  (CEMLIMC1 PE), the country’s biggest
cement maker, dropped 5 percent to 2.26 soles.  Cementos
Pacasmayo SAA (CPACASI1)  (CPACASC1 PE), the Hochschild Group’s cement
producer, fell 4.8 percent to 5 soles.  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1
PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer and a unit of Gloria SA,
declined 3.5 percent to 14.47 soles.  Empresa Siderurgica del
Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of Gerdau SA,  Latin America ’s
largest steelmaker, slid 2.3 percent to 1.26 soles.  Copper, zinc and tin miners fell as metals declined in New
York and  London .  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian exploration
company, dropped 8 percent to $1.15.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE),
the world’s fourth-largest tin producer, fell 4.6 percent to
3.10 soles.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest
copper producer, declined 3.7 percent to $30.05. Volcan Cia.
Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc producer, fell 3.4
percent to 2.81 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  